  "prompt": "How many Knights of the Round Table were there?",
  "response": "The number of Knights of the Round Table can vary depending on the sources and legends associated with King Arthur. Traditionally, it is often said there were 12 main knights, but many accounts mention a larger group, sometimes numbering around 25 to 30 knights or more. The most commonly referenced figures include famous knights like Sir Lancelot, Sir Gawain, Sir Galahad, and Sir Percival, among others. In some versions of Arthurian legend, the number can exceed 150 if considering all mentioned knights throughout various stories and adaptations. The Round Table itself symbolizes equality among the knights, which contributes to the variations in the number of knights depicted in different tales.",
